<br>
Someone suggested being polite and asking the group in /tell if you could have a camp, well let me say that yesterday in Seb I did just this.  I was blatantly told &quot;no&quot; you can't.  Well just because you can take and hold 6 camps doesn't mean you should continue to do so when the zone starts filling up.  This person said &quot;When discos becomes available you can have NG.  We've been here since 8 am and are not giving up a camp now.&quot;  LOL how's that for greedy.  By this point it was at least 4 hours later and they still would not give up a camp.  Hmmmmm well after sitting and waiting for a bit we decided to leave because it wasn't worth the argument anymore.<br>
<br>
Just for the record, the GM said that although they don't necessarily recognize camps per se, they do NOT accept AE grouping in a zone if it means that said AE group is monopolizing a zone.  It breaks the PnP.  I was told to go back and ask nicely for a camp at which time I told the GM that I had politely asked twice and was told to get lost and would not do it again.  Apparently the GM zoned into Seb, there were only 13 players in zone but many corpses.  Hmmmmm interesting I thought.  Little while later zone back in and 1 camp open but the AE group still there.  6 hours and counting but they know added discos to their &quot;camp check&quot; response.  Oh but wait, NG was camped by another group.  How absolutely generous of them.  For the other dozen or so who called &quot;camp check&quot;, sorry about your luck.  <br>
<br>
Sometimes it only takes a few people to ruin it for others.  It would have been different if the AE group was willing to share but with &quot;camp check&quot; answers like &quot;in/out/hallways/disco/chef/jail, yes we're AEing so buzz off&quot; it really leaves a sour taste in a person's mouth.  Welcome to EQ.<br>
