<span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: chuckles at the drama</span><hr size=1> What I'd really love to see is a zone board. (I know it doesn't have much of a place in an RPG but since when is EQ really a RPG?)<br>
<br>
-------------<br>
<br>
/zonecount levelstart levelend<br>
<br>
ex:<br>
<br>
/zonecount 52 60<br>
<br>
Welcome to Everquest. Here is a breakdown of the zone levels you requested:<br>
<br>
Name / players in zone / current spawns<br>
Chardok / 23 / 38<br>
Sebilis / 12 / 45<br>
Velketor's / 40 / 2<br>
Dragon Nec / 6 / 63<br>
<br>
etc..<br>
<br>
Since there aren't truly &quot;camps&quot; in each zone, the utility could at least list how many people are there, and how many mobs are currently alive. <br>
<br>
I equate this to Disney's &quot;Current wait time&quot; board you find at the front of all their theme parks.  How is this much different?<br>
<br>
Oh well.. I can dream. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/uprienmt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>prienmt</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Qeynos Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#628CBC>(8/2/02 12:38:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=38.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: chuckles at the drama</span><hr size=1> aoe groups in seb rarely take all the mobs they claim.  i usally just sit around and pull there mobs anyhow if i go to seb.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#628CBC>- </font><a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards>Morell-Thule Forums</a><font color=#628CBC> - </font><a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm3>Rants</a> <font color=#628CBC> - </font><a href="http://sevendragons.net">Morell-Thule Community Website</a><font color=#628CBC> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.9.5.4<br>Copyright ©1999-2002 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

